name: Razorback
description:
Used to be mounted on a military rocket-carrying truck. Today it's utilized by Scavengers to carry massive cargo.

Only one engine can be mounted on a vehicle.

name: Ammo pack
description:
Increases ammo and missile reserves by 30%.
When destroyed, explodes and deals 250 damage in 2 m radius.

name: Cheetah
description:
A V8 engine with a turbocharger has exceptional parameters for quick retreats from anomalous zones and hot spots.

Only one engine can be mounted on a vehicle.

name: Expanded ammo pack
description:
Increases ammo and missile reserves by 110%.
When destroyed, explodes and deals 450 damage in 2 m radius.

name: Hardcore
description: An old V-eight engine from the middle of the past century that still holds many surprises.  “Just some piffle from the scrap, but it pumps your pistons alright!” (P. Pete)  Only one engine can be mounted on a vehicle.

name: Chameleon Mk2
description:
Makes the vehicle completely invisible for 10 sec. Attacking or receiving damage disables the effect.

Only one invisibility module can be installed on a vehicle.

name: Chameleon
description:
Makes the vehicle completely invisible for 6 sec. Attacking or receiving damage disables the effect.

Only one invisibility module can be installed on a vehicle.

name: Apollo IV
description:
Adds 4 energy points.
When destroyed, explodes and deals 450 damage in 3 m radius.
Only one generator can be mounted on a vehicle.

name: Dun horse
description:
An engine from a small truck, perfectly fine for leisurely exploring the Wasteland.

Only one engine can be mounted on a vehicle.

name: Colossus
description:
A tank engine with incredible power output.

Only one engine can be mounted on a vehicle.

name: Hot red
description: A powerful inline-four with a charger.  “Catch and punish! If it tries something funny, repeat! Any questions?” (P. Pete)  Only one engine can be mounted on a vehicle.

name: Fuel barrel
description:
Allows to receive fuel in missions. Gives 5 fuel. Does not stack with multiple barrels.
Upon destruction explodes and deals 200 damage in 3 m. radius.

name: Hermes
description: While active, pushes the car in the given direction. Can accelerate a vehicle and even launch it upwards. Consumes fuel and takes time to cool down.

name: Car jack
description: This device can flip your vehicle without the help of other players.

name: Radio
description: Increases radius of information transmission to allies to 450 m.

name: Golden Eagle
description:
A V12 from an old military plane. Easily moves a couple of extra tonnes, but it's a bird that can never fly.

Only one engine can be mounted on a vehicle.

name: Fuel tank
description: Does not affect a vehicle's characteristics, but looks so cool!

name: Neutrino
description:
Two zoom levels and target weak spot detection — everything an experienced sniper needs.
Also increases enemy detection radius to 400 m.

name: Aegis-Prime
description: Projects a spherical protective field absorbing all damage from fast projectiles and energy streams.

name: Genesis
description:
Contains spare parts and mechanisms for instant assembly of small devices.
Increases the number of launches for any drones and turrets by 0.25%.
Upon destruction explodes and deals 200 damage in 2 m. range.

name: Oppressor
description:
An armored car with an extremely powerful 12-valve engine that can blow away everything in its path: small obstacles, sleepy raiders, a roof...

Only one engine can be installed on the vehicle.

name: Tormentor
description: With this hardware, all melee weapons start to spin like crazy and hurt everyone even more for $spell_duration$ sec.

name: Contact 2M
description:
Want to shoot some targets with a friend, but he keeps driving away?
Just couple his vehicle to yours!
You and your ally should both install the module “Contact 2M”, activate it and get the crafts as close together as possible. One module can only be used to attach to a single vehicle.

name: Oculus VI
description:
This Dawn's Children prototype was “borrowed” by Scavengers. The module turns towards the hidden enemy, blinks and beeps. With this gadget, nobody else can take you by surprise!
Invisibility detection range up to $detection_radius$ m.
Enemy detection range up to $radar_radius$ m.
